-- Main syntactic lemma: a 0-edge HomTerm is structural.
--
-- Proceeds by induction on `g`.  For atomic constructors, route via
-- `Atomic-non-Agen‚ÜíStructural` (and explicitly rule out `Agen`).  For
-- compound constructors, split the additive 0 into both summands.

nE-0‚ÜíStructural
  : ‚àÄ {A B} (g : HomTerm A B) ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0 ‚Üí Structural g
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (Agen _)              ()
nE-0‚ÜíStructural id                    _ = structural-id
nE-0‚ÜíStructural Œª‚áí                    _ = structural-Œª‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural Œª‚áê                    _ = structural-Œª‚áê
nE-0‚ÜíStructural œÅ‚áí                    _ = structural-œÅ‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural œÅ‚áê                    _ = structural-œÅ‚áê
nE-0‚ÜíStructural Œ±‚áí                    _ = structural-Œ±‚áí
nE-0‚ÜíStructural Œ±‚áê                    _ = structural-Œ±‚áê
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (œÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ñ)             _ = structural-œÉ ‚¶É s ‚¶Ñ
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (h ‚àò k) g-nE‚â°0 =
  -- `nE ‚ü™ h ‚àò k ‚ü´ = nE ‚ü™ k ‚ü´ + nE ‚ü™ h ‚ü´` definitionally (see `nE-‚àò`
  -- in AtomicCompound.agda ‚Äî note the order: it's `nE k + nE h`).
  structural-‚àò
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural h (m+n‚â°0‚áín‚â°0 (nE ‚ü™ k ‚ü´) g-nE‚â°0))
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural k (m+n‚â°0‚áím‚â°0 (nE ‚ü™ k ‚ü´) g-nE‚â°0))
nE-0‚ÜíStructural (h ‚äó‚ÇÅ k) g-nE‚â°0 =
  structural-‚äó
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural h (m+n‚â°0‚áím‚â°0 (nE ‚ü™ h ‚ü´) g-nE‚â°0))
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural k (m+n‚â°0‚áín‚â°0 (nE ‚ü™ h ‚ü´) g-nE‚â°0))

