-- Discharge the original postulate.
--
-- `Atomic f` + `nE ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚â° 0` ‚áí `Structural f` (rules out `Agen`).
-- For the atomic shapes routed into the `‚Ä¶-0E` case from
-- `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`, the atomic-side edge count is
-- 0 by construction (see `nE-{id,Œª‚áí,Œª‚áê,œÅ‚áí,œÅ‚áê,Œ±‚áí,Œ±‚áê,œÉ}` there) ‚Äî we
-- recover that here by case-splitting on the `Atomic` witness rather
-- than threading the edge-count proof through the API.

-- The originally-postulated lemma.  Note: the `Atomic f` hypothesis
-- combined with the dispatch from `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`
-- guarantees that `f` is *not* `Agen` (the Agen branch routes to
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-Agen-compound-1E` instead).  We extract a
-- `Structural f` witness by case-analysis on `Atomic f`, where the
-- `Agen` branch is dismissed via the iso witness's edge-count
-- transport (a `Fin 1 ‚Üî Fin 0` contradiction).

decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Atomic f ‚Üí Compound g
  ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
  ‚Üí decode-rel f ‚âàTerm decode-rel g
decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E {f = f} {g = g} af cg g-nE‚â°0 iso =
  Structural-coherence
    (atomic‚Üístructural af)
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural g g-nE‚â°0)
    iso
  where
    -- The `Agen` branch of `Atomic f` is incompatible with
    -- `‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´` when `nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0`: the iso induces a
    -- bijection `Fin 1 ‚Üî Fin 0`, which is absurd.  We discharge it by
    -- routing `œà : Fin (nE ‚ü™ Agen _ ‚ü´) ‚Üí Fin (nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´)` and then
    -- transporting along `nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0`.
    open import Data.Fin using (Fin; zero)
    open import Relation.Binary.PropositionalEquality using (subst; sym)

    Fin-zero-empty : Fin 0 ‚Üí ‚ä•
